						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Tribhuvanachchakravarttigaḷ Kulōttuṅga (III) Year 20: 1198 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that a certain lady Naṅgaiyāṇḍi, who is described as the daughter of the queen of the <hi rend="italic">ūr</hi>, gifted cows for a twilight lamp. And the same was entrusted to the shepherds Ponnan, son of Aruḷāḷan, Koṅgan and Tiruppagavan. They received the sheep and agreed to burn the said lamp perpetually. </p>						

